Class ListDateSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.domain.invoice.DateSequence
      • gw.api.domain.invoice.BoundedDateSequence
        • gw.api.domain.invoice.ListDateSequence
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<org.joda.time.DateTime>

    public class ListDateSequence
extends BoundedDateSequence
    A ListDateSequence is a date sequence that contains a given set of dates in increasing order (i.e., from earliest/oldest to newest/latest/most-recent). It cannot contain duplicate dates.

    tyoung
